# Memory-note schema (the project note standard)

> This is **the** note format for the in-repo memory graph under `Memory/`
> (decisions + notes). Each note is one markdown file with frozen-v1 frontmatter
> plus an Observations / Relations body. The schema is the canonical bonsai
> standard — downstream hub ingest / repo indexers parse these files directly,
> so the keys are fixed; fill in the values, don't rename the keys.

A memory note lives at `{memory_dir}/{decisions,notes}/<permalink>.md` and looks
like this:

```markdown
---
schema_version: 1
title: <note title>
type: decision | note | fact | log
permalink: <stable-slug>
tags: []
scope: project/<slug>
valid_from: 2026-06-13
superseded_by: null
---
## Observations
- [category] one fact per bullet #tag
## Relations
- relation_type [[Target Note]]
```

## Frontmatter fields

| field | type | required | rule |
|-------|------|----------|------|
| `schema_version` | int | yes | must be `1` |
| `title` | string | yes | non-empty |
| `type` | enum | yes | one of `decision`, `note`, `fact`, `log` |
| `permalink` | string | yes | `[a-z0-9-]` only; out-of-charset is an error, never indexed; unique within the tree |
| `tags` | list[str] | no | default `[]` |
| `scope` | string | yes | `project/<slug>` — `<slug>` must match the manifest `slug` |
| `valid_from` | date | no | `YYYY-MM-DD` if present; scaffolded notes emit it, hand-authored notes may omit it |
| `superseded_by` | string \| null | no | absent ≡ `null` ≡ not-superseded (no missing-key error); if non-null it must resolve to an existing permalink |

## Body

- **`## Observations`** — one fact per bullet. Lead with a `[category]` tag and
  end with inline `#tags` where useful: `- [decision] chose X over Y because Z #arch`.
- **`## Relations`** — typed links to other notes using wikilink targets:
  `- relates_to [[other-permalink]]`. A relation (or `superseded_by`) that points
  at a not-yet-existing note is a **warning**, not an error — forward references
  are legal while the graph is being built out.

The permalink is the note's stable identity — keep it fixed even if the title
changes, since relations and `superseded_by` resolve by permalink.
